Description: Fragment of round handle at neck join from a Brindisi pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine orange-buff. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Latin inscription.
Curator's comments: cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) nos 183, 283
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1291)
